increased%20by%20more%20than%20half%20a%20percentage%20point%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20a%20common%20signal%20of%20imminent%20recession.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glassdoor.com%2Fresearch%2Fjobs-report-preview-september-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnemployment%20claims%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20information-sector%20workers%20have%20doubled%20compared%20to%20a%20year%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20pandemic%20aside%2C%20are%20now%20on%20par%20with%20the%20highest%20levels%20since%202013.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20truth%20is%20that%20the%20pressures%20of%20the%20broader%20economy%20are%20not%20the%20main%20cause%20of%20a%20sag%20in%20tech-worker%20satisfaction.%20Many%20other%20industries%20have%20felt%20the%20squeeze%20of%20higher%20interest%20rates%20and%20their%20spillover%20to%20consumer%20spending%2C%20but%20none%20have%20seen%20their%20employees'%20satisfaction%20dip%20as%20significantly%20as%20Silicon%20Valley.%20The%20underlying%20reasons%20for%20the%20unhappiness%20among%20tech%20workers%20have%20been%20building%20for%20some%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20strike%20at%20the%20very%20heart%20of%20the%20industry's%20once-vaunted%20conventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20hoodies%20to%20neckties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20core%20of%20the%20tech%20industry's%20current%20malaise%20is%20an%20aging%20corporate%20culture.%20Glassdoor%20employee-satisfaction%20data%20reveals%20two%20big%20changes%20that%20have%20been%20unfolding%20over%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20predating%20but%20accelerated%20by%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glassdoor.com%2Fresearch%2Fjobs-report-preview-february-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagementization%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20of%20tech.%20Over%20the%20past%20five%20years%20or%20so%2C%20the%20ratio%20of%20front-line%20workers%20to%20managers%20has%20deteriorated%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20there%20are%20more%20managers%20for%20every%20%26quot%3Bmaker%26quot%3B%20in%20tech%20than%20before.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20before%20layoffs%20aimed%20to%20flatten%20organizational%20hierarchies%2C%20the%20number%20of%20front-line%20jobs%20was%20more%20or%20less%20where%20it%20stood%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20while%20the%20number%20of%20managerial%20jobs%20was%209%25%20higher.%20Economy%20wide%2C%20there%20were%20on%20average%206.6%20front-line%20workers%20per%20manager%20in%202018%20and%202019%2C%20but%20post-pandemic%2C%20the%20ratio%20dropped%20to%206%20to%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20trend%20is%20not%20unique%20to%20the%20tech%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20visible%20in%20industries%20like%20finance%20and%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20sharp%20contrast%20from%20the%20historically%20flat%20hierarchies%20at%20companies%20that%20fueled%20the%201990s%20tech%20boom%20and%20a%20jarring%20shift%20for%20employees%20who%20were%20used%20to%20a%20more%20direct%20line%20to%20the%20top.%20Of%20course%2C%20many%20tech%20managers%20also%20perform%20front-line%20tasks%20such%20as%20coding%20or%20data%20analysis%2C%20and%20some%20managers%20manage%20processes%20instead%20of%20people%20(for%20instance%2C%20transportation%20managers).%20It's%20possible%20that%20as%20tech%20companies%20have%20grown%20into%20more%20complex%20organizations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-great-flattening-organization-meta-tech-layoffs-firing-2023-3%5C%22%3Emore%20management%20layers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20necessary.%20But%20the%20underlying%20result%20is%20the%20same%3A%20The%20people%20building%20the%20products%20are%20increasingly%20removed%20from%20the%20people%20making%20strategic%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20it's%20an%20open%20secret%20that%20the%20best%20jobs%20in%20tech%20aren't%20necessarily%20technical.%20The%20workers%20at%20big%20tech%20companies%20who%20report%20the%20highest%20job%20satisfaction%20in%20Glassdoor%20reviews%20aren't%20in%20technical%20or%20builder%20roles%20like%20engineering%20or%20science.%20While%20non-STEM%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20for%20instance%2C%20in%20human%20resources%20and%20marketing%20%E2%80%94%20can%20and%20often%20do%20contribute%20to%20cutting-edge%20technological%20innovations%2C%20they%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20focus%20on%20supporting%20and%20enabling%20the%20core%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FtxOS8%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Tech%20worker%20job%20satisfaction%20by%20occupation%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22519%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20asking%20why%20the%20employees%20furthest%20from%20the%20technical%20frontier%20are%20happier%20in%20their%20jobs%20than%20those%20making%20the%20actual%20products.%20Perhaps%20it's%20that%20they%20are%20more%20grateful%20for%20the%20opportunity%2C%20suspecting%20that%20their%20job%20opportunities%20might%20be%20bleaker%20in%20other%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sentiment%20suggested%20by%20the%20writer%20Kristi%20Coulter%20in%20her%20recently%20published%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fus.macmillan.com%2Fbooks%2F9780374600907%2Fexitinterview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememoir%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20her%20decade-long%20career%20at%20Amazon.%20Or%20perhaps%20the%20rankings%20reflect%20overextended%20and%20under-resourced%20technical%20ranks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unavoidable%20truth%20is%20that%20working%20at%20the%20most%20familiar%20standard-bearers%20of%20tech%20has%20become%20a%20lot%20like%20working%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20economy%3A%20High%20pay%20is%20usually%20justified%20by%20a%20more%20demanding%20schedule%20and%20longer%20workdays%20(and%20often%20%26quot%3Bwork%20weekends%26quot%3B).%20This%20evolution%20isn't%20unusual%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20well-trodden%20path%20for%20past%20generations%20of%20industry%20innovators.%20With%20time%2C%20they%20become%20bigger%2C%20more%20stable%2C%20and%20more%20routine.%20The%20tech%20titans%20of%20prior%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20from%20Ford%20Motor%20Company%20in%20the%201920s%20to%20Intel%20in%20the%201990s%20%E2%80%94%20were%20once%20workplace%20innovators%20but%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20boring%2C%20corporate%20giants%20as%20they%20aged%20into%20staples%20of%20the%20global%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECan%20tech%20turn%20it%20around%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20is%20not%20lost%20for%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20however.%20Recapturing%20the%20spark%20of%20innovation%20among%20employees%20will%20require%20executives%20to%20recalibrate%20their%20organizational%20compass%3A%20flatten%20org%20structures%2C%20focus%20on%20the%20long%20horizon%20so%20that%20employees%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20feel%20stable%20in%20their%20roles%2C%20and%20re-prioritize%20investment%20in%20the%20core%20technical%20talent%20that%20drives%20the%20development%20of%20crucial%20products.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFundamentally%2C%20it's%20about%20listening%20to%20and%20elevating%20the%20voices%20of%20front-line%20employees.%20When%20the%20workers%20directly%20involved%20in%20creating%20the%20technology%20are%20allowed%20to%20speak%20up%2C%20unconventional%2C%20bold%20ideas%20tend%20to%20bubble%20up.%20By%20asking%20questions%20beyond%20the%20senior%20management%20echo%20chamber%2C%20engaging%20employees%20one-on-one%2C%20and%20creating%20spaces%20for%20employees%20to%20voice%20their%20hopes%20and%20hunches%20in%20psychologically%20safe%20forums%2C%20tech%20companies%20can%20not%20only%20reignite%20their%20workplace%20culture%20but%20also%20better%20serve%20customers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20productive%20communication%20has%20perhaps%20become%20harder%20in%20an%20era%20of%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%20but%20we%20shouldn't%20pretend%20that%20it%20comes%20effortlessly%20in%20the%20office%20either.%20It's%20a%20starkly%20different%2C%20humbler%20skill%20set%20from%20the%20TED%20Talk%20theatrics%20and%20fundraising%20prowess%20that%20drove%20tech%20success%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%20To%20shake%20tech%20workers%20out%20of%20their%20recent%20funk%20and%20get%20the%20industry%20back%20on%20a%20path%20of%20innovation%2C%20companies%20need%20to%20start%20listening%20to%20their%20builders%20again%20and%20empower%20them%20to%20do%20what%20they%20do%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faaron-terrazas%5C%22%3EAaron%20Terrazas%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20chief%20economist%20at%20Glassdoor%2C%20providing%20research%2C%20analysis%20and%20commentary%20on%20today's%20evolving%20workplace%20and%20fast-changing%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-employees-dissatisfied-jobs-new-data-labor-market-glassdoor-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697535242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652d88428bed706e837d93f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-employees-dissatisfied-jobs-new-data-labor-market-glassdoor-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20buildup%20of%20layers%20of%20corporate%20management%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20sclerotic%20environment%20that%20is%20weighing%20on%20frontline%20tech%20employees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Aaron%20Terrazas)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-employees-dissatisfied-jobs-new-data-labor-market-glassdoor-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BDidn't%20Your%20Father%20Teach%20You...%26quot%3B%3A%20Gavaskar%20