rld-europe-67131128.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Popular%20Flowering%20Plant%20Can%20Give%20You%20A%20Heart%20Attack%2C%20Warn%20Experts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFoxglove%2C%20scientifically%20known%20as%20Digitalis%2C%20is%20a%20distinctive%20flowering%20plant%20renowned%20for%20its%20elegant%2C%20tubular%20blossoms%20and%20rich%20history%20in%20herbal%20medicine.%20Native%20to%20Europe%20and%20Asia%2C%20it%20has%20become%20a%20beloved%20garden%20favourite%20worldwide.%20Its%20tall%20spikes%20decked%20with%20pendulous%2C%20trumpet-shaped%20flowers%20in%20various%20shades%20of%20pink%2C%20purple%2C%20and%20white%20add%20a%20touch%20of%20enchantment%20to%20any%20garden.%20However%2C%20Foxglove's%20allure%20is%20not%20only%20aesthetic%20-%20it%20contains%20potent%20compounds%2C%20like%20digoxin%2C%20a%20type%20of%20cardiac%20glycoside%20that%20has%20a%20powerful%20effect%20on%20the%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20popular%20saying%20about%20foxglove%2C%20including%20that%20one%20that%20talks%20about%20the%20flower%20giving%20a%20person%20a%20heart%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20is%20that%20true%3F%20Here's%20what%20expert%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFoxgloves%20contain%20extremely%20potent%20compounds%20called%20cardiac%20glycosides%20-%20'cardiac'%20for%20their%20function%20on%20the%20heart%20muscle%20and%20'glycosides'%20to%20indicate%20that%20these%20compounds%20have%20sugar%20molecules...%20to%20help%20the%20body%20absorb%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Zhen%20Wang%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fchemistry%2Fcan-foxgloves-really-give-you-a-heart-attack%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20healthy%20heart%20pumps%20blood%20across%20the%20body%20through%20thousands%20of%20cardiac%20cells%20that%20contract%20for%20the%20process%20to%20be%20completed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20membranes%20of%20these%20cells%20have%20different%20ion%20channels%20and%20transporters%2C%20which%20permit%20charged%20particles%20like%20sodium%2C%20potassium%20and%20chloride%2C%20said%20the%20%3Cem%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fem%3E%20report.%20Movement%20of%20these%20ions%20generates%20electrical%20current%20and%20the%20sodium-potassium%20pump%20maintains%20the%20electrical%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20foxglove%20species%20produce%20some%20amount%20of%20these%20cardiac%20glycosides%2C%20such%20as%20digoxin%2C%20and%20they%20bind%20very%2C%20very%20tightly%20to%20the%20sodium-potassium%20pump%2C%20inhibiting%20it%20so%20the%20transporter%20cannot%20pump%20those%20ions%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Zheng%20Wang.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDeactivating%20this%20pump%20causes%20a%20cascade%20of%20chemical%20problems%20within%20the%20cardiac%20cells%20that%20combine%20to%20make%20the%20heart%20suddenly%20beat%20much%20harder%20and%20much%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20disruption%20in%20the%20heart's%20natural%20rhythm%2C%20a%20dangerous%20type%20of%20arrhythmia%20known%20as%20ventricular%20fibrillation%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20sudden%20cardiac%20arrest%20and%20even%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20digoxin%20is%20also%20known%20for%20its%20valuable%20heart%20medication.%20%26quot%3BDigoxin%20is%20clinically%20prescribed%20for%20heart%20failure%20when%20other%20drugs%20have%20failed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Wang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20advised%20that%20if%20someone%20accidentally%20ingests%20any%20part%20of%20the%20plant%2C%20they%20should%20immediately%20go%20to%20a%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697529540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F4dqdadm8_foxglove_625x300_17_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fpopular-flowering-plant-can-give-you-a-heart-attack-warn-experts-4488422%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Foxglove%20is%20a%20flowering%20plant%20that%20is%20native%20to%20Europe%20and%20Asia%2C%20but%20has%20become%20a%20beloved%20garden%20fa