lished%22%3A1697526900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-belgian-police-shooting_6323991.jpg%3F20231017073047%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbrussels-shooting-what-we-know-about-suspected-terror-attack-before-belgium-v-sweden-match-12986005%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20Swedish%20people%20were%20shot%20dead%20and%20a%20third%20person%20was%20wounded%20in%20an%20attack%20in%20Brussels%20last%20night.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbrussels-shooting-what-we-know-about-suspected-terror-attack-before-belgium-v-sweden-match-12986005%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbrussels-shooting-what-we-know-about-suspected-terror-attack-before-belgium-v-sweden-match-12986005%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbrussels-shooting-what-we-know-about-suspected-terror-attack-before-belgium-v-sweden-match-12986005%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Refuses%20to%20Legalise%20Marriage%20Equality%2C%202%20of%205%20Judges%20Say%20Queer%20Couples%20Must%20Be%20Given%20Legal%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20(October%2017)%20delivered%20its%20judgment%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20case.%20The%20court%20was%20in%20agreement%20that%20marriage%20equality%20overall%20must%20be%20decided%20by%20parliament%20and%20cannot%20be%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20judgment%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%20whether%20marriage%20equality%20is%20legalised%20is%20something%20parliament%20must%20decide%20on%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20within%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20remit%20to%20create%20new%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20the%20state%20must%20recognise%20queer%20unions%2C%20even%20without%20marriage%2C%20and%20provide%20legal%20safeguards%20and%20rights%20to%20them.%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%20agreed%20with%20this%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20other%20three%20judges%20on%20the%20bench%20did%20not%20agree%20with%20this%20directive.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20comprised%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%2C%20Justice%20Ravindra%20Bhat%2C%20Justice%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20Justice%20P.S.%20Narasimha.%20A%20total%20of%20four%20judgments%20were%20delivered%2C%20with%20%E2%80%9Ca%20degree%20of%20agreement%20and%20a%20degree%20of%20disagreement%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20bench%20has%20confined%20the%20case%20to%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%201954%20and%20clarified%20that%20it%20will%20not%20deal%20with%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%20or%20personal%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20four%20judgements%20today%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20ability%20of%20queer%20couples%20adopt%20children.%20While%20the%20chief%20justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20and%20the%20second%20senior-most%20judge%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%20held%20that%20the%20Central%20Adoption%20Resource%20Authority%20(CARA)%20had%20exceeded%20its%20authority%20in%20barring%20unmarried%20and%20queer%20couples%20from%20adopting%20children%2C%20their%20three%20colleagues%20on%20the%20bench%20did%20not%20agree%20with%20them.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20proposition%20that%20queer%20persons%20could%20adopt%20children%20was%20struck%20down%2C%203%3A2.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20was%20looking%20at%20the%20legality%20of%20Regulation%205(3)%20of%20the%20CARA%20Regulations%20for%20adoption.%20Regulation%205%20lays%20down%20the%20criteria%20for%20those%20adults%20who%20wish%20to%20adopt%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Queerness%20is%20not%20urban%20or%20elite%E2%80%99%3A%20CJI%20Chandrachud%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%20his%20judgment%20dealt%20with%20the%20issue%20of%20judicial%20review%20and%20separation%20of%20powers.%20Queer%20people%20exist%20across%20all%20communities%20and%20settlements%2C%20urban%20or%20rural%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Constitution%20demands%20this%20Court%20protects%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens.%20Doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20does%20not%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20this%20Court%20issuing%20directions%20for%20the%20protection%20of%20fundamental%20rights%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20Justice%20Chandrachud.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CQueerness%20is%20not%20urban%20or%20elite%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20has%20titled%20one%20section%20of%20his%20judgment.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20an%20English%20speaking%20man%20with%20a%20white%20collar%20man%20who%20can%20claim%20to%20be%20queer%20but%20equally%20a%20woman%20working%20in%20an%20agricultural%20job%20in%20a%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Queerness%20can%20be%20regardless%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20caste%20or%20class%20or%20socio-economic%20status.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20was%20responding%20to%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20argument%20in%20court%20that%20this%20issue%20only%20pertains%20to%20the%20urban%20elite.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMarriage%20is%20not%20static%2C%20the%20CJI%20said%20in%20his%20order.%20%E2%80%9CWithdrawal%20of%20the%20State%20from%20the%20domestic%20space%20leaves%20the%20vulnerable%20party%20unprotected.%20Thus%20all%20intimate%20activities%20within%20private%20space%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20beyond%20State%E2%80%99s%20scrutiny%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20then%20questioned%20whether%20the%20court%20could%20strike%20down%20Section%204%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20in%20the%20present%20batch%20of%20petitions%2C%20this%20Court%20holds%20that%20Sec%204%20of%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20is%20unconstitutional%20because%20of%20being%20under-inclusive%2C%20it%20has%20to%20either%20strike%20it%20down%20or%20read%20it%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20is%20struck%20down%2C%20it%20will%20take%20the%20country%20to%20pre-independence%20era.%20If%20the%20Court%20takes%20the%20second%20approach%20and%20reads%20words%20into%20the%20SMA%2C%20it%20will%20be%20taking%20up%20the%20role%20of%20legislature%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20is%20not%20equipped%20to%20undertake%20such%20an%20exercise%20of%20reading%20meaning%20into%20the%20statute.%20Whether%20a%20change%20in%20the%20regime%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20is%20for%20the%20Parliament%20to%20decide.%20%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20right%20to%20enter%20into%20a%20union%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20one%E2%80%99s%20partner%20and%20the%20right%20to%20recognition%20of%20that%20union%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20if%20such%20queer%20associations%20are%20not%20recognised%2C%20it%20can%20thwart%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChoosing%20a%20life%20partner%20is%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20choosing%20one%E2%80%99s%20course%20of%20life.%20Some%20may%20regard%20this%20as%20the%20most%20important%20decision%20of%20their%20life.%20This%20right%20goes%20to%20the%20root%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20liberty%20under%20Article%2021.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20court%20has%20recognised%20that%20queer%20persons%20cannot%20be%20discriminated%20upon.%20Material%20benefits%20and%20services%20flowing%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20and%20denied%20to%20queer%20couples%20will%20be%20a%20violation%20of%20their%20fundamental%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20talked%20about%20adoption%20laws%20and%20said%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20only%20married%20heterosexual%20couples%20can%20make%20for%20good%20parents.%20%E2%80%9D%20CARA%20Regulation%205(3)%20indirectly%20discriminates%20against%20atypical%20unions.%20A%20queer%20person%20can%20adopt%20only%20in%20an%20individual%20capacity.%20This%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20reinforcing%20the%20discrimination%20against%20queer%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6The%20CARA%20circular%20(which%20excludes%20queer%20couples%20from%20adoption)%20is%20violative%20of%20Article%2015%20of%20the%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandrachud%20said%20he%20had%20a%20disagreement%20with%20parts%20of%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20judgment.%20%E2%80%9CContrary%20to%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20judgment%2C%20directions%20in%20my%20judgment%20does%20not%20result%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20institution%2C%20rather%20they%20give%20effect%20to%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20under%20Part%203%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20then%20read%20out%20the%20directions%20he%20was%20issuing.%20These%20include%20creating%20hotlines%20and%20safe%20houses%20for%20queer%20couples%20and%20spreading%20awareness%20about%20how%20queerness%20is%20natural%2C%20and%20ordering%20the%20police%20not%20to%20harass%20queer%20people%20by%20unnecessarily%20summoning%20them%20to%20police%20stations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETowards%20the%20end%20of%20his%20judgment%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20could%20not%20change%20or%20re-read%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20to%20allow%20for%20marriage%20equality%2C%20as%20that%20falls%20in%20the%20remit%20of%20parliament.%20However%2C%20he%20argued%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfailure%20of%20the%20state%20to%20recognise%20the%20bouquet%20of%20rights%20flowing%20from%20a%20queer%20relationship%20amounts%20to%20discrimination%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRight%20to%20enter%20into%20union%20cannot%20be%20restricted%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20sexual%20orientation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20record%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20that%20the%20Union%20Government%20will%20constitute%20a%20committee%20to%20decide%20the%20rights%20and%20entitlements%20of%20persons%20in%20queer%20unions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20The%20committee%2C%20he%20said%2C%20shall%20consider%20including%20queer%20couples%20as%20family%20in%20ration%20cards%2C%20enabling%20queer%20couples%20to%20name%20each%20other%20as%20nominees%20in%20bank%20accounts%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENecessary%20to%20recognise%20civil%20unions%3A%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20S.K.%20Kaul%20read%20out%20his%20judgment%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20agree%20with%20the%20judgment%20of%20CJI.%20It%20is%20not%20res%20integra%20for%20a%20constitutional%20court%20to%20uphold%20the%20rights%20and%20the%20court%20has%20been%20guided%20by%20the%20constitutional%20morality%20and%20not%20social%20morality.%20These%20%5Bqueer%5D%20unions%20are%20to%20be%20recognised%20as%20a%20union%20to%20give%20partnership%20and%20love%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kaul.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%20said%20he%20disagreed%20with%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20the%20SMA%20was%20passed%20solely%20to%20allow%20for%20heterosexual%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNon-heterosexual%20unions%20and%20heterosexual%20unions%20must%20be%20seen%20as%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20coin%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kaul%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20moment%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20remedy%20the%20historical%20injustice%20and%20discrimination%20and%20thus%20governance%20needed%20to%20grant%20rights%20to%20such%20unions%20or%20marriages.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20supported%20the%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20call%20for%20an%20anti-discrimination%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLegal%20recognition%20of%20non-heterosexual%20unions%20is%20a%20step%20towards%20marriage%20equality%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kaul%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECourt%20can%E2%80%99t%20ask%20state%20to%20create%20legal%20status%20for%20queer%20couples%3A%20Justice%20Ravindra%20Bhat%20and%20Hima%20S.%20Kohli%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Ravindra%20Bhat%20then%20read%20out%20the%20judgment%20signed%20by%20him%20and%20Justice%20Hima%20Kohli.%20While%20they%20agreed%20with%20much%20of%20what%20the%20CJI%20had%20said%2C%20Justice%20Bhat%20said%20the%20two%20disagreed%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20directives.%20They%20said%20they%20agreed%20with%20Justice%20Narasimha%E2%80%99s%20concurring%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Bhat%20said%20that%20over%20time%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20has%20gone%20through%20several%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20particularly%20subscribe%20to%20the%20views%20of%20CJI%20on%20democratising%20intimate%20spaces%E2%80%A6these%20outcomes%20were%20brought%20by%20legislative%20acts%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20While%20courts%20have%20intervened%20several%20times%20when%20queer%20people%20have%20faced%20violence%2C%20that%20is%20part%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20duty%20to%20protect%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20court%20has%20recognised%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20social%20institution.%20Marriage%20as%20an%20institution%20precedes%20the%20state.%20This%20implies%20that%20marriage%20structure%20exists%20regardless%20of%20the%20state.%20Terms%20of%20marriage%20are%20independent%20of%20the%20state%2C%20and%20its%20sources%20are%20external%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Bhat%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20Justice%20Bhat%20said%2C%20cannot%20require%20the%20state%20to%20create%20legal%20status%20for%20queer%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20agree%20that%20there%20is%20a%20right%20to%20relationship%2C%20we%20squarely%20recognise%20that%20it%20falls%20within%20Article%2021.%20It%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20partner%20and%20intimacy.%20They%20are%20like%20all%20citizens%20entitled%20to%20enjoy%20their%20right%20without%20hindrance%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20However%2C%20he%20continued%20that%20the%20court%20cannot%20provide%20relief%20in%20matters%20pertaining%20to%20the%20creation%20or%20change%20in%20a%20social%20institution%20(marriage).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20cannot%20be%20an%20unqualified%20right%20to%20marry%20which%20is%20to%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Bhat%20said%20%E2%80%93%20something%20the%20CJI%20too%20had%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20consenting%20adults%20may%20always%20choose%20to%20live%20together%20and%20be%20intimate%2C%20the%20judge%20said%2C%20despite%20whatever%20others%20may%20say.%20They%20also%20have%20the%20right%20to%20be%20protected%20from%20violence%20when%20living%20in%20that%20way%2C%20and%20the%20right%20to%20live%20with%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20difficulties%20in%20creating%20through%20a%20judicial%20diktat%20a%20right%20to%20civil%20union%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Bhat%20said.%20The%20court%20cannot%20create%20a%20legal%20framework%20for%20queer%20couples%20and%20it%20is%20for%20the%20legislature%20to%20do%20so%2C%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20queer%20persons%20have%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20their%20partners.%20But%20the%20state%20cannot%20be%20obligated%20to%20recognise%20the%20bouquet%20of%20rights%20flowing%20from%20such%20a%20Union.%20We%20disagree%20with%20the%20CJI%20on%20this%20aspect%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Bhat%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20SMA%20cannot%20be%20read%20in%20a%20gender-neutral%20manner%2C%20as%20that%20would%20lead%20to%20unseen%20consequences%20and%20could%20be%20detrimental%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20denial%20of%20benefits%20such%20as%20a%20PF%2C%20pension%20and%20so%20on%20to%20queer%20partners%20may%20be%20discriminatory%2C%20Justice%20Bhat%20said.%20However%2C%20the%20solicitor%20general%20had%20already%20said%20that%20a%20committee%20would%20be%20formed%20to%20look%20into%20such%20required%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Bhat%20also%20said%20that%20he%20disagreed%20with%20the%20CJI%20on%20the%20right%20of%20queer%20couples%20to%20adopt.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20unmarried%20or%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20good%20parents..%20..given%20the%20objective%20of%20section%2057%2C%20the%20state%20as%20parens%20patriae%20has%20to%20explore%20all%20areas%20and%20to%20ensure%20all%20benefits%20reach%20the%20children%20at%20large%20in%20need%20of%20stable%20homes%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConferring%20legal%20status%20to%20civil%20union%20can%20only%20be%20through%20enacted%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Bhat%20said%20in%20his%20conclusions.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20these%20findings%20will%20not%20preclude%20the%20right%20of%20queer%20persons%20to%20enter%20into%20relationships.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20constitutionally%20permissible%20to%20recognise%20a%20civil%20union%3A%20Justice%20P.S.%20Narasimha%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Narasimha%20agreed%20with%20the%20conclusions%20of%20Justice%20Bhat.%20The%20constitutional%20challenge%20to%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20and%20Foreign%20Marriage%20Act%20must%20fail%20for%20the%20reasons%20given%20by%20Justice%20Bhat%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20review%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20legislative%20framework%20in%20this%20case%20requires%20deliberative%20exercise%20and%20for%20the%20same%2C%20the%20legislature%20is%20entrusted%20to%20do%20so%20constitutionally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20reserved%20its%20order%20in%20the%20case%20on%20May%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20for%20the%20petitioners%20had%20argued%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESpecial%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20as%20it%20stands%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20discriminatory%20because%20of%20its%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20and%20that%20this%20denial%20of%20access%20to%20marital%20institutions%20meant%20inferiority%20and%20subordination.%20They%20also%20said%20there%20is%20a%20duty%20in%20the%20Union%20to%20recognise%20the%20association%20of%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20as%20married%20couples%20in%20a%20non-discriminatory%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESolicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20had%20opposed%20the%20petitions%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697526869000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmarriage-equality-supreme-court-decision%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20proposition%20that%20queer%20couples%20could%20adopt%20children%20was%20also%20struck%20down%2C%203%3A2.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmarriage-equality-supreme-court-decision%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Killers%20of%20the%20Flower%20Moon%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Black%20Lies%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98All%20of%20Us%20Strangers%E2%80%99%20Among%20Main%20Competition%20Films%20at%20Camerimage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697525973000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FKillers_Of_The_Flower_Moon__Photo_01032.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235758674%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22EnergaCamerimage%2C%20the%20cinematography-focused%20film%20festival%20set%20for%20Torun%2C%20Poland%2C%20for%20Nov.%2011